message="""\
subject: The Foreign Students are Suffering

Dear admission committee,
This letter’s content has been drafted and agreed on by the international students who study in universities in China and students who are studying in mainland China.
The duty of this letter is to speak for what every foreign student whether studying online or in mainland China endures during this period since the pandemic has launched and how it influences negatively their educational path. This perplexing situation has affected the quality of learning and from driving the educational system to advance and develop students’ skills to inevitably restricting them into memorizing lessons and focusing on achieving good scores that qualify them to take university without considering students’ competence and skills that goes beyond that and which is difficult to detect and work on through online classes. The causes that restrict students from going back to China and pursue their studies regularly are definitely rational and purely protective and understood by the students. But as time passed, and vaccinations launched, it rises a hope among all students to enroll back to their universities which clearly means that the students are not satisfied with the quality of learning they are receiving now.
We made a list that discloses the cons of online classes and right after a list of solutions suggested to the situation:
• Time difference: it is very hard for students from all around the world to cooperate with china ‘s time to join their classes.
• Routine : Students are restricted from  performing activities that develop their learning skills and creativity.
• Majors : Some majors require traineeship and work in the terrain, and cannot acquire enough knowledge through online classes.
• International students in mainland China : Foreign students are incapable to go back to their hometown as they have to let go of their duties in China since they can’t go back and forth.
• Scholarships : Students don’t get scholarship’s living expenses, and face difficulties to work and study at the same time.
• Majors in Chinese : The lack of practice for international students studying in Chinese language to improve their language level and live in an atmosphere that helps acknowledging the culture.
This was briefly some of the main cons of online classes. Moving to the solutions, here is a list of students’ requests to solve the situation.
• Vaccinations: Students must be vaccinated before leaving their land.
• Planning: Gradual enrollment of students.
• Test: students should be ready to take PCR test before having the access to enter the universities and within 24hours.
• Quarantine: students agree to spend from 14to28days in quarantine to guarantee their and other’s safety.
• Students must abide to China’s rules of protection from the virus and should take responsibly the precautionary measures.
In the hope that this letter will get to the Chinese government and Chinese universities and the hope that it will be taken in consideration, as this letter is one of the many calls and trials students have made to obtain a satisfying but also a safe solution that can be beneficial for both sides, by that we can say that it has all been illustrated waiting for you highly respected committee to take in consideration this situation and find convenient solutions.
Currently, we are waiting for an immediate response from Chinese universities, as well as from the Chinese government regarding this matter that we are dealing with as foreign students.
As international students, we still have no clue when P.R.China will open its borders and more importantly not being recognized from your part as it's almost 2 years and half waiting for a reply for our question " when P.R.China will open its borders for international students ?".
Last but no least, we hope that the Chinese government will come out with a solution for international students outside P.R.China,as we are willing to abide all regulations ( tests, quarantine, ... ) setteled by the Chinese government.
In the coming days, you will receive such a huge number of messages concerning this issue. We have tried all solutions available so that to reach our goal without getting any reply. Our question is so simple and need to be answered from your part as soon as possible: will P.R.China will open its borders for international students by September 2022 ?
Looking forward for your immediate response via this email
( liuxuesheng.zhongguo@outlook.fr ) 
Sincerely yours,
International students
"""
message=message.replace("•","-")
message=message.replace(u"\u2018", "'").replace(u"\u2019", "'")#replace ’


